    "(5) ROI = Final cash -Initial cash Initial cash * 100%.",
    "(2) Sharpe Ratio (SR) SR is a widely used metric in finance for assessing the risk-adjusted performance of an investment or trading strategy.",
    "In the context of Bitcoin trading, SR measures the average return generated by the trading strategy, relative to the risk-free rate, per unit of risk, as represented by the standard deviation of the returns.",
    "The higher the SR, the better is the risk-adjusted performance of the trading strategy.",
